rComments: The Prof is alright, you can tell she cares about her students, however, the course is entirely memorization. 100%. I have never taken a pure memorization course before this and man was it hard. Do not take if you're not good with that. She could have made it more application based however you're expected to just regurgitate everything on the tests

Took ANT101 and ANT211 with her. She's hilarious and gives hints for tests/exams throughout the term. Tests are easy! If you come to lecture, you're pretty much good. Prof. Fukuzawa is so cute and funny; you'd always have a good time in her class.

This course is an amazing course dont get me wrong but that is because of the amazing guest lecturers. The assignments are not the best and ask you to write a lot despite not being worth a lot. Also, she isnt always the best when asked a question, it was as if she didnt even read my email.
easy midterms and final exam. super fun to listen to in lecture.
Shes witty, welcoming and so importantly, not boring. Shes accepting of students and encourages students to reach out to her, and become more involved.

She is really approachable and so nice. She makes the material easy to understand. her lectures are entertaining and you gotta go to find out what to expect on tests. The labs are fun and easy. Highly recommend.
Amazing prof. Really funny and kind. She seems to care about her students and goes out of her way to make sure everyone understands. Make sure you go to lectures or you will not pass.

Make good notes, read the textbook material she says to and memorize what she emphasizes is important and you should secure an A. Labs are easy and the tests are literally only multiple choice, so take this course if youre good with that.

Shes the best professor I had this semester. Very funny in lecture, engaging, slips in great anecdotes from time to time. Best of all shes extremely passionate about what she teaches, and is very humbling and nice. Her exam is mostly a rehash of past years, and if you study you should do fine. Her tests have some weird questions, but she curves.

I actually look forward to attending her lectures because they are entertaining and you get to be involved (meaning easier to grasp material for the test) I find that her short answer tests are much better than her multiple choice. If you participate and engage in the class you will do well
for one test there was a question that was really unfair because she never taught us about it and it was never in the textbook so that wasn't cool. other than that she talks fast

rComments: she's extremely funny and makes lecture enjoyable. HOWEVER, her tests are absolute sh*t and she talks way too fast during lecture. she also gives a ton of hints about tests and exams. textbook is absolutely useless to the course as well.

rComments: SHE IS AWESOME

I love Sherry with all my heart. She is a textbook example of a professor who truly loves what she does. the type of prof you would wanna have coffee with. she ta'd for my tutorial sometimes and those were honestly the best ones. Her exam is killer though. the course in general is really content heavy even though she gives a lot of hints ;) #ralph

She spoke clearly and slowly in her lectures. Her tests were somewhat easy. Once you finish the book, you have to start reading the articles and they are long! (some were interesting). I was doing fine until the final. Hardest final I ever had and brought my grade really low. Overall all: prof is great/ course is hard (but interesting).

Professor Fukuzawa is the best prof I have had at UTM. She is engaging and smart and a great teacher! Osteo is a heavy course but it was my favourite because she is excited to teach and good a giving tips for understanding and remembering the bones. She was very accessible throughout the course and ready to answer any questions I had.

rComments: The prof made this class so interesting for me! She was so funny, sweet and easy to understand. She would thoroughly explain assignments to make sure people did well and she would always help make sure everyone is prepared for tests. If you do the work, you'll get a good mark, even if you don't have a biology background like myself!

She speaks sooooooooo fast!!! and she doesn't even cover everything in the lecture from her own lecture outline document. With that being said I did pretty well in the course just because I read the entire textbook, articles, watched the movies and memorized lecture notes. It wasn't hard just medicorely do everything before the tests.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'So many papers']

rComments: This prof is really approachable and super friendly. Her lectures are interesting, enthusiastic and really clear.  She is very helpful and she seems to really want everyone to do well. You must attend her lectures to do well in this course.

Kukuzawa is a great prof and very funny! She gives lots of hints and constantly repeats questions she will be putting on the midterm and exam, so I definitely recommend attending her lectures. The practicals are super easy and are there to boost your mark which is great. Although it was a mandatory course for me, I would definitely take it again.
You do the minimum in this class by just reading lecture notes and you can get a 95 shes easy , right to the point and no tricks up her sleeve, easily the best bird course at UTM

I took ANT101 with Fukuzawa a long time ago and fell in love with this subject, in part, due to her. She has a great personality, brings a great deal of enthusiasm to class and out the classroom is very helpful. Her relaxed personality will make you love this course.   Honestly, I'd nail her if I could.

SHE IS AWESOME!! She teaches with enthusiasm and you can tell she is passionate about anthropology cares a lot about her students. She gives so many hints about what will be tested, you just need to put in the work to memorize the facts.

Took her Ant101 course over the summer, and she was amazing. Her lectures are very interesting. You must attend lectures in order to pass the course. The tests are straight forward, no curve balls at all. It's a great course to take over the summer, one of my faves so far.
Very interesting lectures. A lot of material. Start memorizing info early.

Dr. Fukuzawa is one of the best professors I've had. She teaches with so much enthusiasm and really makes the lectures worth going to; she also gives a lot of hints as to what will be on the quizzes/exam. If you put in the effort, you can easily get an A. She is amazing!!!
Great Prof!
Great prof, funny, keeps you interested, good looking

Prof. Fukuzawa is one of the best professors I have had as a first-year. Her lectures are clear-cut and she always hints at content on the quizzes and the final exam. In fact, her lectures are refreshing and quite entertaining; though she does speed through it a bit (granted, it is an hour lecture). Quizzes are straightforward and the exam is easy!

Overall just NOT A GOOD professor  lectures are extremely fast and extremely boring. She clearly does not like her job I really don't understand why she is a professor and why students pay copious amounts of money to watch movies and barely learn anything from a miserable person.

She lectures fast, sometimes to much information thrown at your face.  Very confusing quizzes.  Professor will not budge grade, even if 69 that could be a 70.  But instead will report to the chair if any such request is made.

i have a science background, so i was familiar with some material. took 101 in the summer,fast paced but so easy to understand. didnt TOUCH the textbook & did pretty well. loved her style of teaching  so i took 211 with her because i knew it would be easy and it is. if shes teaching a course then it will the closest to a bird course at utm there is

Dr. Fukuzawa is awesome. This class is a second year science course and I'm a first year non-science student and I'm passing! The class wasn't what I expected to be at first but the concepts are easy to grasp if you pay attention and take good notes. Lectures are a bit fast paced but if you can manage to get the main points down you'll do fine!

Very interesting and engaging lectures. Very straightforward, gives lots of helpful hints for studying. Repeats things multiple times to make sure you understand. Also very nice and approachable, would definitely take another course with her.

ANT101 was my science distribution credit for first year. It was very hard because there was so much information. Expect to read 150-200 pages a week for the class. AND if you do not read these pages then do not expect to pass the course. Proff Fukuzawa made the course very clear and told us exactly how to study for the test.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Hilarious', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: She's alright, she explains concepts really well and she can be pretty funny sometimes. The only setback might be tests.... but since the material she teaches is usually interesting, it usually works out in the end somehow. If you have no prior science background at all, probably not best to take it with her....

She is so funny and her lectures are interesting! If you can find good textbook notes you don't have to read the textbook. Worksheets are completed in tutorials so you have to attend to get the marks, but they're also really helpful and enjoyable.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Hilarious', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: A very easy course
shes awesome, inspirational and makes the lecture material so interesting. this class was super fun and opened new opportunities for me.
love her

She is such an awesome prof. Very clear and concise. Gives you hints as to what would be on the tests (which is very rare among professors). With that said, you have to go to class and pay attention. Barely read the textbook and left the class with a 4.0. Labs were super easy and great mark boosters.

Amazing lecturer. She explains concepts in a simple manner, but not simplistic. She is straight to the point, and does not add extra details and keeps things interesting. She is very clear about what she expects (rarely seen in profs), is fair and approachable when there are any questions. There should be more profs like her.
Amazing course. The prof is very organized and her lectures are interesting and clear. She is very friendly and easy to talk to. I would love to take another course with her.
My fav prof by far! took a bio related course only because the prof makes the material understandable and enjoyable. would recommend the prof any day for any course :)
This prof is amazing.  She is so approachable and she makes the material easy to learn and interesting.  I would love to take another course with her.

Prof is great, but TA is not. TA teaches a large portion of the course and she's not helpful. You can't really ask her too many questions during the labs. I don't think she likes it.It's better to learn it on your own. This course would be better if TA  was more helpful and didn't mind answering questions.Prof thinks the ta is brilliant though.
Amazing and interesting and such a great lecturer!
EXCELLENT LECTURER! Great class, very clear, easy to do well if you pay attention to what she says. Very friendly and accessible.
Amazing lectures and labs.  Prof is very helpful and easy going.  She really makes this subject interesting and I would definitely take another course with her.
EXCELLENT lecturer, but not personable at all. I asked her a question one time after class and she just glared at me until I walked away...
I liked her..nice proff...but sometimes the subject gets extremely boring and bogged down my factual info
great lectures
fun

I would definitely take another course with this professor. She makes the lectures very interesting and she is very clear about what to expect on the tests. She is also very approachable and friendly. She really made an effort to help me do well in the course.

had her for both 102 and 331 and she's okay. she still says 'Riiigght' a million times but the 331 had lots of interesting videos. my friends made her out to be this super great teacher but she's just average. i wouldnt retake another course with her as its all MCQ or T/f

She is a wonderful person, who has a passion for her craft. She is extremely approachable and light-hearted. She genuinely cares about her students' well beings and goes above and beyond to deliver the material in an interesting and creative manner. Always ready to help and re-explain, far assignments, good TA's as well
The prof is very organized and friendly. I found the lectures interesting. Her grading is fair - but make sure that you listen for her hints. I would take another course with her.

A very warm, approachable, and light-hearted professor. Generous with grading. To do well in the course, just follow all her instructions. Textbook isn't so great with many factual errors conflicting with the lecture material, however be prepared to memorize it word for word.

I felt a little ripped off that every class only ended up being 1 hour instead of the scheduled 2. Fukuzawa is a great professor though, really nice and approachable. We got stuck with a crap TA this year, but she was very helpful remarking assignments. I recommend taking this class and defintely look at past tests!  Also, read the books!

This proff is boring. She just goes on and on about anthro but the material is sometimes dry. She could use some class-interaction techniques. Shes also a tough marker, so if you took ANT102 with Barac and want to continue to ANT101, get ready to see your grade droppp. Its not worth an elective but for the people majoring in anthro, I hope it worke
This course is AMAZING! It is the best course I have taken at UTM.  The prof. is really enthusiastic and the tests and assignments are fair.
The prof makes this course material very interesting.  Her lectures are clear and organized.  She is very approachable and friendly.

The material is very simple, however the tests are very detailed and half is based on textbook questions which are very detailed. There is no consistency in the grading of assignments, and there was a lack of communication between the TA and the prof. Overall would not take it again, hard to do very well (ie-85+)
This was a really great course.  The lectures are interesting and the prof is friendly.
This prof is great! She is friendly and her lectures are interesting.  The tests are hard, but the grading if fair.
the course is interesting and the grading was fair
this professor is very clear, organized and approachable.
I liked her.  Lectures were interesting, and assignments were marked fairly.  Also gives lots of time for assignments.

Flexible yet rigid. Gives plenty of time (e.g. whole term) for assignments but they are marked hard with little feedback. Also goes fast in lectures and writes difficult tests (imo). Welcomes students to visit her during office hours.

Do NOT take ANT 334 with her.  She goes extremely fast and gives way too much info, most of which is unnecessary.  The bell ringer tests are really hard as well...have to answer 5 questions in 1 min.  She's much better in ANT 331.
